NAME
    App::BrowserOpenUtils - Utilities related to Browser::Open

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.002 of App::BrowserOpenUtils (from
    Perl distribution App-BrowserOpenUtils), released on 2019-05-28.

SYNOPSIS
DESCRIPTION
    This distribution includes several utilities:

    #INSERT_EXECS_LIST

FUNCTIONS
  open_browser
    Usage:

     open_browser(%args) -> [status, msg, payload, meta]

    This function is not exported.

    This function supports dry-run operation.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   all => *true*

    *   urls* => *array[str]*

    Special arguments:

    *   -dry_run => *bool*

        Pass -dry_run=>1 to enable simulation mode.

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (payload) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

